{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_27","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed for `com.google.code.gson:gson:2.3`. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-4832-fails-java-run-com.google.code.gson-gson-2.3-87cf349d\n\nThe most likely failing stage is the initial JVM test run. `human-intervention-logs/com.google.code.gson:gson:2.3/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T08-03-27-309860Z.log` shows `:test` failing inside `:tckTest` with two `NoSuchMethodException`s:\n- `UnsafeAllocatorAnonymous2Test` looks for `com.google.gson.internal.UnsafeAllocator$2.<init>(java.lang.reflect.Method)`\n- `UnsafeAllocatorAnonymous3Test` looks for `com.google.gson.internal.UnsafeAllocator$3.<init>(java.lang.reflect.Method,int)`\n\nThe fix-generation log suggests the likely root cause is a mismatch in the 2.3 test expectations for `UnsafeAllocator$2` vs `$3`: `human-intervention-logs/com.google.code.gson:gson:2.3/fix-java-run-fail/pi-generation-2026-05-03T08-04-49-304790Z.log` contains a generated patch that swaps those constructor signatures and updates the related native-image test metadata. However, the run never produced a real change: `stats/com.google.code.gson/gson/2.3/execution-metrics.json` shows `status: failure`, `iterations: 1`, `generated_loc: 0`, and the starting and ending commit are both `363d8093d8873ee8ed645aea684b4fffac6b4f7e`.\n\nThere is also downstream fallout after the failed fix attempt. `human-intervention-logs/com.google.code.gson:gson:2.3/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-03T08-05-24-531631Z.log` reports `MissingResourceRegistrationError` for `META-INF/services/org.junit.platform.launcher.PostDiscoveryFilter`, and `human-intervention-logs/com.google.code.gson:gson:2.3/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log` reports `Missing reachability-metadata.json` under `metadata/com.google.code.gson/gson/2.3/`.\n\nPlease inspect:\n- `human-intervention-logs/com.google.code.gson:gson:2.3/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T08-03-27-309860Z.log`\n- `human-intervention-logs/com.google.code.gson:gson:2.3/fix-java-run-fail/pi-generation-2026-05-03T08-04-49-304790Z.log`\n- `human-intervention-logs/com.google.code.gson:gson:2.3/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-03T08-05-24-531631Z.log`\n- `human-intervention-logs/com.google.code.gson:gson:2.3/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`\n\nNext steps:\n1. Manually fix the 2.3 JVM tests so the reflective constructor expectations for `UnsafeAllocator$2` and `UnsafeAllocator$3` match Gson 2.3, then rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=com.google.code.gson:gson:2.3`.\n2. Once the JVM lane passes, add or regenerate `metadata/com.google.code.gson/gson/2.3/reachability-metadata.json` and rerun `./gradlew checkMetadataFiles -Pcoordinates=com.google.code.gson:gson:2.3`.\n3. Re-run native verification and, if it still fails, address the missing JUnit service resource registration reported in `cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-03T08-05-24-531631Z.log`."}}
